COPS are ready for a safe and crime-free festive season.Lieutenant-Colonel Lungelo Dlamini, Gauteng provincial police spokesman, said as festive season crime operations are gaining momentum, the SAPS, Metro police and other law enforcement agencies have declared war against criminals.Dlamini said over the weekend four high calibre firearms, a shotgun, 12 pistols, more than 200 rounds of ammunitions and many other items, including police uniform were seized.- During a shoot-out between cops and the suspects, a police officer was wounded and three people died, including two suspects and a civilian in Riverlea. A police officer is recovering well in hospital.Dlamini said cases including of murder, attempted murder and possession of unlicensed arms and ammunition will be some of the charges facing the 20 arrested suspects.- In Midrand, members of the Johannesburg Metro police who were doing a stop and search operation spotted a suspicious grey Mercedes Benz vehicle which failed to stop. A chase then ensued until the suspicious vehicle lost control at the corner of Mimosa and Garden roads.&ldquo;One suspect was arrested.&rdquo; Dlamini added while investigations are continuing, one of the suspect arrested in Midrand may be linked to several outstanding cases including ATM bombings, posing as a members of the SAPS, business robberies and attacks on members of the police. Suspects will appear at the various Magistrate Courts in the province.- The public is urged to report suspicious people and vehicles. Information that may lead to arrest and conviction of criminals involved in serious and violent crime may be rewarded.You may forward any information to Crime Stop at 08600 1011 or to the nearest police station.